    <h2 {...{
      "id": "install"
    }}>{`Install`}</h2>
    <Tabs block={true} defaultValue="daemon" values={[{
      "label": "As a Daemon",
      "value": "daemon"
    }]} mdxType="Tabs">
      <TabItem value="daemon" mdxType="TabItem">
        <p>{`The `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/setup/deployment/strategies/#daemon"
          }}>{`daemon deployment strategy`}</a>{` is designed for data
collection on a single host. Vector runs in the background, in its own process,
collecting `}<em parentName="p">{`all`}</em>{` data for that host.
Typically data is collected from a process manager, such as Journald via
Vector's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/journald/"
          }}><inlineCode parentName="a">{`journald`}</inlineCode>{` source`}</a>{`, but can be collected
through any of Vector's `}<a parentName="p" {...{
            "href": "/docs/reference/sources/"
          }}>{`sources`}</a>{`.
The following diagram demonstrates how it works.`}</p>
        <DaemonDiagram platformName={null} sourceName={null} sinkName={null} mdxType="DaemonDiagram" />
        <hr></hr>
