      }}>{`deployment section`}</a>{` for more info on how to
deploy Vector.`}</p>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "administering"
    }}>{`Administering`}</h2>
    <p>{`Vector can be managed through the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://github.com/Homebrew/homebrew-services"
      }}>{`Homebrew services`}</a>{`
manager:`}</p>
    <Jump to="/docs/administration" mdxType="Jump">Administration</Jump>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "uninstalling"
    }}>{`Uninstalling`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`brew remove vector
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "updating"
    }}>{`Updating`}</h2>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`brew update && brew upgrade vector
`}</code></pre>
    <h2 {...{
      "id": "package"
    }}>{`Package`}</h2>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "architectures"
    }}>{`Architectures`}</h3>
    <p>{`Vector's Homebrew packages only support the X86_64 arhcitecture.`}</p>
    <h3 {...{
      "id": "versions"
    }}>{`Versions`}</h3>
    <p>{`Historical Vector versions can be found in the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://vector.dev/releases/latest/"
      }}>{`releases`}</a>{`.
Once you've found the version you'd like to install you can specify it with:`}</p>
    <pre><code parentName="pre" {...{
        "className": "language-bash"
      }}>{`brew install vector@X.X.X
`}</code></pre>
    <p>{`Due to limitations of Homebrew, Vector cannot pin specific major or minor
versions. If this is a requirement, then we recommend installing Vector
directly `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "/docs/setup/installation/manual/from-archives/"
      }}>{`from an archive`}</a>{`.`}</p>
